displayName: Lasra Forest, in front of the cave

parameters:
"There's a cave up ahead, but we've walked quite a distance
to get here."

"Shall we stay here for the night and start exploring the
inside of the cave thoroughly from tomorrow?"

"Stay overnight with just the two of us? I could go
investigate the monsters in the cave right now, you know?"

(So far, he doesn't seem to be up to anything, but Maroges
is definitely someone to keep an eye on.)

"Yes, of course I understand that, but, well... I'm quite
tired myself."

"My legs are swollen and it's difficult to walk any
further."

(Is he plotting something? But he shouldn't know that I'm
watching him closely.)

(If Maroges really is connected to a human trafficking
organization, going along with his plan might reveal some of
his methods.)

"Lacking stamina, are we? Well, alright. It's not good to
rush and get injured, so let's rest and prepare for
tomorrow."

"But you do understand, I hope you're not planning
anything."

(Well, even if he tries something, I'll capture him in a
moment.)

"No, no, even if I were to try something, you'd turn the
tables on me."
"But what about your duties as a swordsman?"
"?Duties as a swordsman? What are you talking about?"

As Tina echoed Maroges' words, a ringing noise suddenly
filled her ears.
"Ah, umm, yes, the duties. I understand."

"Not fulfilling them would be a disgrace as a swordsman, so
you'll have to bear with me regardless."
"Is that so? Well then, I must do my best."
"Hehehe, then let's go inside and get started right away."
And so, the two of them entered the rest area.
HP and MP have been fully restored.
